WEBVTT

00:21.648 --> 00:25.151
<i>The sun 'll come out tomorrow</i>

00:25.318 --> 00:29.864
Bet your bottom dollar that tomorrow

00:30.031 --> 00:32.867
There 'll be sun

00:33.034 --> 00:37.247
Just thinking about tomorrow

00:39.207 --> 00:41.501
Clears away the cobwebs
And the sorrow

00:41.668 --> 00:44.212
Till there's none

00:44.379 --> 00:49.884
When I'm stuck with a day
That's gray and lonely

00:50.051 --> 00:52.137
I just stick out my chin

00:52.303 --> 00:57.100
And grin and say

00:57.267 --> 01:02.939
Oh, the sun 'II come out tomorrow

01:03.106 --> 01:07.485
<i>So you gotta hang on till tomorrow</i>

01:07.652 --> 01:11.072
Come what may

01:11.239 --> 01:14.117
Tomorrow, tomorrow

01:14.284 --> 01:16.953
I love ya, tomorrow

01:17.120 --> 01:21.708
You're only a day away

01:21.875 --> 01:25.962
Tomorrow, tomorrow

01:26.129 --> 01:29.007
I love ya, tomorrow

01:29.174 --> 01:33.887
You're only a day

01:34.053 --> 01:38.975
A Way

02:22.519 --> 02:26.314
Maybe far away

02:26.481 --> 02:31.444
Or maybe real nearby

02:31.611 --> 02:35.865
He may be pouring her coffee

02:36.032 --> 02:40.703
She may be straightening his tie

02:40.870 --> 02:44.290
Maybe in a house

02:44.457 --> 02:49.087
All hidden by a hill

02:49.254 --> 02:53.591
She's sitting playing piano

02:53.758 --> 02:57.262
<i>He's sitting paying</i> a <i>bill</i>

02:57.846 --> 03:01.599
Betcha they're young
Betcha they're smart

03:01.766 --> 03:05.395
Bet they collect things
Like ashtrays and art

03:05.562 --> 03:10.316
Betcha they're good
Why shouldn't they be?

03:10.483 --> 03:16.406
Their one mistake was giving up me

03:18.491 --> 03:23.288
So maybe now it's time

03:23.454 --> 03:28.084
And maybe when I wake

03:28.251 --> 03:33.006
<i>They'll be there calling me baby</i>

03:33.172 --> 03:38.052
Maybe

03:59.824 --> 04:01.659
Annie!

04:02.452 --> 04:03.828
Annie!

04:15.214 --> 04:19.427
It's okay.
Everything's gonna be all right.

04:19.677 --> 04:21.471
There, there.

04:22.263 --> 04:25.600
It was only a dream, Molly.
It's all right.

04:25.850 --> 04:28.269
How am I supposed to get any sleep?

04:28.519 --> 04:32.106
It was only a dream.
Everything's all right.

04:32.357 --> 04:34.817
Molly shouldn't be in this room.

04:35.193 --> 04:39.322
She's a baby.
She cries all the time.

04:39.572 --> 04:41.074
She wets the bed.

04:41.699 --> 04:42.992
I do not!

04:43.242 --> 04:45.870
You're the one who shouldn't
be in here!

04:46.079 --> 04:49.415
- Brat, stop!
- We're gonna get in trouble.

04:49.666 --> 04:50.875
Go, Duffy! Go!

04:51.125 --> 04:54.420
Oh, my goodness! Oh, my goodness!

04:55.129 --> 04:56.923
Cut it out!

04:57.507 --> 05:01.302
I mean it! Do you want
Miss Hannigan to come in?

05:01.552 --> 05:04.013
Go back to bed.

05:06.265 --> 05:10.895
Now. Or you'll have me to deal with.

05:11.104 --> 05:14.065
Blow it out of your old Wazoo.

05:21.948 --> 05:24.867
Close your eyes.
Think about your folks.

05:25.076 --> 05:29.372
You're the only one who has folks.
Mine are dead.

05:29.706 --> 05:31.874
Think of folks
who want to adopt you...

05:32.125 --> 05:36.337
...because they want a little girl with
brown hair and brown eyes.

05:38.339 --> 05:42.093
Betcha he reads
Betcha she sews

05:42.301 --> 05:45.763
Maybe she's made me
A closet of clothes

05:46.556 --> 05:48.099
Maybe they're strict

05:48.266 --> 05:51.144
As straight as a line

05:51.310 --> 05:57.984
Don't really care
As long as they're mine

05:58.151 --> 05:59.944
Oh, my goodness.

06:00.153 --> 06:04.949
So maybe now this prayer's

06:05.116 --> 06:09.537
The last one of its kind

06:09.704 --> 06:14.625
Won't you please
Come get your baby?

06:35.980 --> 06:39.734
Did I hear singing in here?

06:46.908 --> 06:49.744
All right. Fine.

06:50.995 --> 06:53.498
Since we're all so wide awake!

06:53.706 --> 06:55.291
Get up! Get out of bed!

06:56.834 --> 07:00.505
Clean up this mess!
Get dressed!

07:00.755 --> 07:05.343
This room had better be regulation
before breakfast...

07:05.593 --> 07:09.680
...my little pig droppings.
Or kill, kill, kill!

07:09.931 --> 07:14.560
- It's in the middle of the night.
-"It's in the middle of the night."

07:15.394 --> 07:20.441
If this floor don't shine like
the top of the Chrysler Building...

07:20.691 --> 07:23.361
...your backsides will.

07:23.569 --> 07:24.612
Understand?

07:24.862 --> 07:28.116
Yes, Miss Hannigan.

07:29.659 --> 07:33.663
- What do we say, Annie?
- I love you, Miss Hannigan.

07:34.956 --> 07:38.751
Why any kid would want to be
an orphan is beyond me.

07:55.101 --> 08:00.565
It's the hard-knock life for us

08:00.731 --> 08:03.192
Instead of treated
We get tricked

08:03.359 --> 08:06.195
Instead of kisses
We get kicked

08:06.362 --> 08:08.865
It's the hard-knock life

08:24.839 --> 08:27.633
Got no folks to speak of

08:27.800 --> 08:30.469
So it's the hard-knock row we hoe

08:30.636 --> 08:33.306
Cotton blankets instead of wool

08:33.472 --> 08:36.100
Empty bellies instead of full

08:36.267 --> 08:38.394
It's the hard-knock life

08:52.533 --> 08:55.661
Don't it feel like the wind
Is always howling?

08:55.828 --> 08:58.539
Don't it seem like
There's never any light?

08:58.706 --> 09:01.542
Once a day, don't you want
To throw the towel in?

09:01.709 --> 09:04.921
It's easier than putting up a fight

09:10.092 --> 09:12.762
No one's there
When your dreams at night get creepy

09:12.929 --> 09:15.473
No one cares if you grow
Or if you shrink

09:15.640 --> 09:18.100
No one dries
When your eyes get red and weepy

09:18.267 --> 09:21.687
From the crying you would think
This place would sink

09:31.822 --> 09:33.866
Empty belly life

09:34.700 --> 09:36.994
Rotten smelly life

09:37.411 --> 09:39.997
Full of sorrow life

09:40.164 --> 09:41.540
No tomorrow life

09:41.707 --> 09:44.460
Santa Claus we never see

09:44.627 --> 09:47.421
Santa Claus, what's that?
Who's he?

09:47.588 --> 09:50.216
No one cares for you a smidge

09:50.383 --> 09:53.052
When you're in an orphanage

09:53.219 --> 09:55.471
It's the hard-knock life

10:06.482 --> 10:08.943
You'll stay up till this dump...

10:09.151 --> 10:13.281
...shines like the top
of the Chrysler Building.

10:16.200 --> 10:17.410
Kill, kill.

10:17.576 --> 10:19.245
Yank the whiskers from her chin

10:19.412 --> 10:20.579
Little pig droppings

10:20.746 --> 10:22.081
Jab her with a safety pin

10:22.248 --> 10:23.416
Rotten orphans.

10:23.582 --> 10:25.126
Make her drink a Mickey Finn

10:25.293 --> 10:28.713
- Nobody loves you.
- I love you, Miss Hannigan.

10:28.963 --> 10:30.798
Get to work!

10:31.590 --> 10:33.718
Strip that bed!

10:34.635 --> 10:36.846
Scrub that floor!

10:48.816 --> 10:51.235
Polish my shoes!

10:52.737 --> 10:54.363
And I mean...

10:54.613 --> 10:56.991
...start now!

10:57.658 --> 10:59.660
It's the hard-knock life for us

10:59.827 --> 11:00.870
Mud in your eye!

11:01.037 --> 11:03.205
It's the hard-knock life for us

11:03.372 --> 11:06.042
No one cares for you a smidge

11:06.208 --> 11:09.003
When you're in an orphanage

11:09.170 --> 11:13.591
It's the hard-knock life

11:13.758 --> 11:17.928
The hard-knock life

11:20.514 --> 11:23.059
We better get out of here
or we'll get killed.

11:23.309 --> 11:26.103
- Cover me up good.
- All you ever do is run away.

11:26.354 --> 11:28.439
Oh, my goodness! Oh, my goodness!

11:28.647 --> 11:30.274
She'll put you in the cellar.

11:30.524 --> 11:33.819
- You'll get whipped again.
- You're gonna get us in trouble.

11:34.070 --> 11:35.446
Molly, shut up!

11:35.654 --> 11:40.451
- I'm gonna tell.
- And I'm gonna rearrange your teeth!

11:41.369 --> 11:42.536
Stomp on her foot!

11:42.745 --> 11:46.207
What are you all
just standing around here for?

11:46.415 --> 11:49.251
You're supposed to clean
the bathroom and kitchen...

11:49.502 --> 11:52.338
...before lunch,
my little pig droppings.

11:52.546 --> 11:56.717
And if you skip the corners,
there will be no lunch.

11:57.218 --> 12:01.097
And we're not having hot mush today.

12:04.934 --> 12:07.144
We're having cold mush.

12:08.145 --> 12:12.817
- What?
- We love you, Miss Hannigan.

12:13.067 --> 12:14.652
Wonderful.

12:15.945 --> 12:16.987
Where's Annie?

12:17.196 --> 12:20.533
- She had to go bathroom.
-"She had to go bathroom."

12:20.783 --> 12:22.993
Miss Hannigan.

12:25.496 --> 12:28.624
- Mr. Bundles.
- Mr. Bundles.

12:44.348 --> 12:48.060
It's time for a tumble with a bundle.

12:48.310 --> 12:50.980
Not today. I'm behind--

12:51.188 --> 12:53.441
My schedule, I mean.

12:53.732 --> 12:57.862
What are schedules in the storms
of passion, Mr. Bundles?

12:58.112 --> 13:01.407
Just so much flotsam and jetsam.

13:01.657 --> 13:03.242
Miss Hannigan, please!

13:06.036 --> 13:08.747
- What are you doing out here?
- Helping you.

13:08.998 --> 13:12.418
- It's heavy today.
- It's a lot heavier than usual.

13:13.043 --> 13:15.838
- It shouldn't be. What's in there?
- Miss Hannigan.

13:16.005 --> 13:17.423
Mr. Bundles.

13:17.590 --> 13:19.091
- Miss Hannigan.
- Yes?

13:19.258 --> 13:22.970
- You're my kind of woman.
- Oh, yes. Yes.

13:23.137 --> 13:25.347
Till next month, Miss Hannigan.

13:27.933 --> 13:29.560
I'll be right here.

13:52.583 --> 13:55.878
Mr. Bundles, I'm in here.

13:59.715 --> 14:02.885
- Thank you, Mr. Bundles.
- Good luck.

15:19.044 --> 15:21.088
Get his tail!

15:23.966 --> 15:25.009
Poor dog.

15:25.551 --> 15:28.429
Leave him alone.
What's he ever done to you?

15:29.221 --> 15:31.307
Amscray!

15:36.729 --> 15:39.440
All right, who's next?

15:45.404 --> 15:46.780
Anybody else?

15:47.031 --> 15:48.824
- Scram, man!
- Let's go!

15:49.033 --> 15:51.535
- Then get lost.
- Let's get a move on!

15:51.702 --> 15:55.122
- Let's hotfoot it!
- Shake a leg! Come on!

15:56.498 --> 15:59.043
Let's go! Come on!

16:05.674 --> 16:07.801
Hey, you're all right.

16:17.269 --> 16:20.939
I didn't do nothing any decent person
wouldn't have done.

16:22.066 --> 16:23.859
Dumb dog.

16:37.456 --> 16:42.503
Dumb dog, why are you following me?

16:42.670 --> 16:45.422
I ainâ€™t got a crumb, dog

16:45.589 --> 16:49.134
How about letting me be?

16:49.301 --> 16:52.054
I ain't gonna feed you

16:52.221 --> 16:55.432
Ain't got a scrap for you
Need you?

16:55.599 --> 16:58.727
Don't give a rap for you, dumb dog

17:00.145 --> 17:02.564
Dumber than they come, dog

17:02.731 --> 17:07.277
You're the most presuming dog

17:07.778 --> 17:13.157
That a human could know

17:24.086 --> 17:26.003
Hey, mister, that's my dog!

17:26.213 --> 17:29.383
Oh, yeah? Where's his license?
Where's his leash?

17:29.633 --> 17:32.261
He's no more your dog
than I am your father.

17:32.469 --> 17:34.471
I left his license at home.

17:34.680 --> 17:38.684
Please don't take him to the pound.
My father's blind.

17:38.892 --> 17:44.231
This dog leads him to work.
If he doesn't work, we'll starve.

17:45.065 --> 17:46.650
What's his name?

17:47.443 --> 17:49.570
My father's name?

17:49.737 --> 17:53.365
- The dog's name.
- Oh, the dog's name!

17:53.615 --> 17:55.492
His name's Sandy.

17:55.743 --> 17:57.077
That's it. Sandy.

17:57.286 --> 17:59.163
Call him.

17:59.621 --> 18:01.248
Call him?

18:02.374 --> 18:04.168
Go over there and call him.

18:04.543 --> 18:06.086
You mean by his name?

18:06.295 --> 18:09.423
By his name. The dog's name.

18:18.724 --> 18:20.976
Sandy! Come here, Sandy.

18:22.811 --> 18:24.605
Sandy! Come here, Sandy!

18:24.813 --> 18:27.024
Here, Rover. Come here, boy.

18:27.274 --> 18:30.068
Rin Tin Tin! Come here.
Come to Daddy.

18:30.277 --> 18:35.324
- Sandy, come here.
- Rin Tin Tin, come here.

18:35.532 --> 18:37.785
Sandy!

18:38.035 --> 18:40.662
Come here, Sandy. Come here, Sandy.
Come here.

18:42.790 --> 18:44.625
Good old Sandy!

18:45.042 --> 18:48.128
You've got yourself a dog.
Get him a collar and a leash.

18:48.378 --> 18:50.047
Yes, sir.

19:27.125 --> 19:30.420
Miss Hannigan! Miss Hannigan!

19:30.629 --> 19:32.172
What?!

19:33.006 --> 19:34.049
Annie!

19:34.258 --> 19:37.386
Look what I found
under a paving stone.

19:37.553 --> 19:39.096
Oh, Annie!

19:39.263 --> 19:43.684
Annie, my little peach fuzz,
are you all right?

19:43.851 --> 19:48.272
- I was worried sick.
- I knew you would be.

19:48.522 --> 19:51.066
A big-hearted woman like you.

19:51.316 --> 19:54.403
How can I ever thank you...

19:54.570 --> 19:55.779
."enough?

19:56.029 --> 19:59.825
I'm sure we can think of something
if we get our heads together.

20:00.075 --> 20:02.244
Kissy, kissy, kissy.

20:02.494 --> 20:05.205
Kill! Kill!

20:13.922 --> 20:19.011
- We love you, Miss Hannigan.
- Sure.

20:24.975 --> 20:28.437
Oh, my goodness! Oh, my goodness!

20:33.025 --> 20:34.318
He smells.

20:34.526 --> 20:37.446
- What's his name, Annie?
- Guess.

20:38.155 --> 20:39.698
Fifi?

20:40.032 --> 20:42.451
That ain't a name for this mutt.

20:43.660 --> 20:46.371
So how about Champion

20:46.538 --> 20:48.832
Champion, you're anything but

20:50.208 --> 20:54.838
- We could call him Tiger
- But there's no bite in him

20:55.047 --> 20:58.342
Tiger
Kittens would frighten him

20:58.508 --> 21:03.972
Rover
When you think it over

21:04.181 --> 21:09.895
Rover is the perfect name
For this dumb-looking dog

21:10.103 --> 21:11.438
Rover!

21:27.245 --> 21:30.374
Sandy, Sandy's his name

21:30.540 --> 21:32.793
If you please

21:33.210 --> 21:36.296
If you don't believe me

21:36.463 --> 21:40.342
Ask any one of the fleas

21:40.634 --> 21:43.470
Residing on Sandy

21:43.637 --> 21:47.099
<i>True he ain't pedigreed, Sandy</i>

21:47.265 --> 21:49.184
There ain't no better breed

21:49.351 --> 21:55.774
And he really comes in handy

21:55.941 --> 21:59.903
Especially when you're all alone
In the night

22:00.070 --> 22:04.241
And you're small
And terribly frightened

22:04.408 --> 22:06.451
It's Sandy

22:06.618 --> 22:11.123
Sandy who'll always be

22:11.707 --> 22:16.920
There

22:17.379 --> 22:19.214
She's coming. She's coming.

22:19.715 --> 22:21.299
Hide him.

22:39.901 --> 22:43.196
I love you, Miss Hannigan.

22:43.447 --> 22:48.201
And you will love the paddle closet,
Annie!

22:48.910 --> 22:50.537
And this...

22:50.996 --> 22:53.707
...will love the sausage factory.

22:54.082 --> 22:56.334
- No, Miss--
- What?

22:57.377 --> 23:01.173
We love you, Miss Hannigan.

23:01.381 --> 23:02.507
Shut up.

23:04.634 --> 23:08.472
Apples, a nickel. Apples here.

23:08.638 --> 23:10.140
Yes, ma'am.

23:10.307 --> 23:13.185
Here you go. Thank you.
God bless you.

23:13.351 --> 23:15.479
Apples here.

23:15.729 --> 23:18.815
Big, delicious apples here.

23:49.554 --> 23:52.015
All right! All right!

23:53.850 --> 23:54.893
Yeah?

23:55.644 --> 23:57.854
Miss Hannigan, I'm Grace Farrell.

23:58.021 --> 24:00.107
The New York Board of Orphans
sent me.

24:02.275 --> 24:05.362
My goodness, won't you come in?

24:05.570 --> 24:07.864
- Thank you.
- Right this way.

24:08.657 --> 24:10.575
Well, welcome.

24:10.742 --> 24:13.245
- Welcome to our happy home.
- Off my foot, Molly!

24:13.411 --> 24:14.454
- Thank you.
- Ladies.

24:14.621 --> 24:16.039
Smell that perfume.

24:16.206 --> 24:18.041
- And your name was?
- Grace Farrell.

24:18.208 --> 24:20.961
- She wants a girl to clean her house.
- Aptly named.

24:21.128 --> 24:24.756
- I bet it's gonna be me!
- I'm here to inquire about an orphan.

24:25.340 --> 24:28.927
Grace, I can explain the whole thing.
What happened was...

24:29.136 --> 24:33.974
...the child bribed Mr. Bundles
to smuggle her out of here.

24:34.224 --> 24:37.519
I should've called Mr. Donatelli,
but the truth is...

24:37.727 --> 24:40.313
...I just saw red,
so I called the cops instead.

24:40.480 --> 24:44.359
Anyway she's back, everything's fine.
All's well that ends well.

24:44.609 --> 24:47.529
No harm, no foul,
my little scissors legs?

24:47.988 --> 24:50.866
What are you talking about?

24:53.285 --> 24:58.415
Are you peddling beauty products?
I don't need beauty products.

24:59.082 --> 25:03.962
If that's what you're doing,
peddle yourself right out of here.

25:04.171 --> 25:08.550
I am the private secretary
to Oliver Warbucks.

25:08.758 --> 25:10.927
The Oliver Warbucks?

25:12.387 --> 25:16.933
- Oliver Warbucks the millionaire?
- No, the billionaire.

25:18.310 --> 25:19.936
Holy Mary, Mother of God.

25:20.145 --> 25:24.816
Mr. Warbucks would like to invite
an orphan to spend a week with him.

25:25.609 --> 25:26.943
I'm here to select one.

25:27.194 --> 25:29.321
That's just wonderful.

25:29.571 --> 25:31.907
What kind of orphan did he
have in mind?

25:32.115 --> 25:33.950
Well...

25:34.117 --> 25:35.660
...friendly.

25:36.411 --> 25:37.454
Intelligent.

25:37.829 --> 25:41.958
M-I-S-S-I-S-S-I-P-P-I.

25:42.792 --> 25:44.002
And I'1aPPY-

25:58.808 --> 26:02.854
- How old?
- Well, age doesn't really matter.

26:05.732 --> 26:07.150
Seven.

26:08.318 --> 26:11.655
Eight. Nine.

26:12.239 --> 26:13.281
Ten?

26:13.490 --> 26:15.408
Yes, 10 is just fine.

26:15.659 --> 26:17.202
Ten?

26:17.369 --> 26:19.663
I'm sorry, I almost forgot.

26:19.829 --> 26:24.584
- Mr. Warbucks prefers red hair.
- A 10-year-old redhead?

26:24.834 --> 26:27.254
Nope. Sorry, ain't got it.

26:27.462 --> 26:29.798
What about this child?

26:30.048 --> 26:32.384
- Annie?
- Yes.

26:34.844 --> 26:36.805
You don't want Annie.

26:37.055 --> 26:38.807
Why not?

26:39.975 --> 26:41.643
She's...

26:41.935 --> 26:43.270
She's a drunk.

26:44.938 --> 26:46.815
Fiddle-faddle.

26:47.065 --> 26:50.568
How'd you like to spend a week
with Mr. Warbucks at his house?

26:51.152 --> 26:55.240
Oh, boy! I would love to.
I would really, really love to.

26:55.490 --> 26:58.118
Wait! Slow down!
Hold on there!

26:58.868 --> 27:02.205
You can have any orphan in the whole
orphanage except Annie.

27:02.372 --> 27:03.415
Why?

27:03.623 --> 27:08.128
She's got it coming to her,
and I don't mean a week of luxury.

27:08.378 --> 27:11.381
- She's got to learn to know her place.
- Her place?

27:11.631 --> 27:13.258
Annie is entirely too cheeky.

27:13.842 --> 27:17.512
- Mr. Warbucks likes cheeky orphans.
- Tough!

27:18.263 --> 27:22.726
I assume your resistance has to do with
Mr. Donatelli and the Board of Orphans.

27:22.976 --> 27:24.978
Don't assume nothing, sweetheart.

27:25.186 --> 27:27.063
Mr. Warbucks knows Mr. Donatelli.

27:27.314 --> 27:29.190
- Is that a fact?
- Yes, it is.

27:29.399 --> 27:34.362
It's also a fact that he said how many
people he had lined up for your job.

27:36.906 --> 27:38.408
- Is that a fact?
- Yes.

27:38.950 --> 27:42.287
It's awful to be out of work,
isn't it, Miss Hannigan?

27:45.248 --> 27:46.708
Just terrible.

27:47.083 --> 27:48.501
Leaping lizards!

27:48.752 --> 27:52.839
-"Leaping lizards."
- The limousine is waiting.

27:56.801 --> 27:58.011
- My dog.
- What?

27:58.803 --> 28:01.014
Here, Sandy. Come here.

28:01.306 --> 28:03.725
He's really nice. Really good.

28:03.933 --> 28:06.644
He never jumps up on people.

28:08.563 --> 28:13.526
He's a very sweet dog, but really,
I don't think Mr. Warbucks--

28:13.735 --> 28:16.237
- Then I'm not coming.
- What?

28:16.488 --> 28:19.157
She's going to send him to
the sausage factory.

28:19.449 --> 28:22.786
- She said so herself.
- I'm not zoned for dogs.

28:22.994 --> 28:26.873
- We'll take the dog.
- Oh, boy!

28:32.670 --> 28:34.214
Bye, Annie!

28:35.799 --> 28:39.177
I'll be back.
I'll bring everybody presents.

28:46.643 --> 28:51.189
Bye, Molly. See you soon.
Bye, Pepper. Bye, Duffy.

29:31.229 --> 29:34.858
Is this a train station?
Are we going on a train?

29:35.066 --> 29:37.819
No, this is Mr. Warbucks' house.

29:44.242 --> 29:45.994
Leaping lizards.

30:00.675 --> 30:05.180
This is Punjab. He and the Asp
are Mr. Warbucks' bodyguards.

30:07.223 --> 30:09.851
Come along. Let's get you settled.

31:17.085 --> 31:18.753
Been to the zoo, Miss Farrell?

31:18.962 --> 31:20.213
Not recently, Drake.

31:20.380 --> 31:22.340
- Has the organ been tuned?
- Yes, miss.

31:22.507 --> 31:23.550
- Pool heated?
- Yes.

31:23.716 --> 31:25.093
- Tennis net up?
- Yes.

31:25.260 --> 31:26.636
- French doors fixed?
- Yes.

31:26.803 --> 31:28.304
- Elevator oiled?
- Yes.

31:28.471 --> 31:29.847
- Typewriter repaired?
- Yes.

31:30.098 --> 31:31.766
- Second Teletype installed?
- Yes.

31:32.016 --> 31:35.812
- Are you allergic to dogs, Drake?
- No, filth.

31:36.062 --> 31:38.481
- Is dinner under way, Mrs. Pugh?
- Yes, miss.

31:38.648 --> 31:41.859
Preparing his favorite.
Texas grapefruit, Virginia ham...

31:42.026 --> 31:47.073
...Idaho potatoes, Wisconsin cheese,
Washington apples and baked Alaska.

31:47.407 --> 31:50.159
I have an announcement to make.

31:50.410 --> 31:54.372
This is Annie, and she'll
be staying with us for a week.

31:54.956 --> 31:56.791
This is her dog, Sandy.

31:57.000 --> 31:59.335
He'll be staying with me.

31:59.502 --> 32:01.504
May I take your sweater, miss?

32:01.713 --> 32:05.008
- Will I get it back?
- Of course, miss!

32:06.551 --> 32:09.554
What would you like to do first?

32:14.892 --> 32:19.814
The windows, then the floors,
that way if I drip--

32:21.399 --> 32:25.945
You don't understand. You don't
have to do any cleaning here.

32:26.112 --> 32:27.488
I won't?

32:27.655 --> 32:29.407
How am I gonna earn my keep?

32:29.574 --> 32:31.868
You're our guest, Annie.

32:32.535 --> 32:35.496
Cecilie will pick out all your clothes

32:35.663 --> 32:38.499
Blue is her best color.
No, red, I think.

32:38.666 --> 32:41.669
Your bath is drawn by Mrs. Greer

32:41.836 --> 32:44.672
Soap. No, bubbles, I think.

32:44.839 --> 32:47.717
Annette comes in to make your bed

32:47.884 --> 32:50.720
The silk? No, the satin sheets, I think.

32:50.887 --> 32:54.432
I think I'm gonna like it here

33:31.260 --> 33:34.263
The swimming pool is down the stairs

33:34.430 --> 33:37.100
Inside the house? Oh, boy!

33:37.266 --> 33:40.353
The tennis court is in the rear

33:40.520 --> 33:43.481
- I never even picked up a racket.
- What?

33:43.648 --> 33:46.234
Have an instructor here at noon

33:46.401 --> 33:49.278
And get that Don Budge fellow,
if he's available.

33:49.445 --> 33:53.741
I think I'm gonna like it here

34:10.800 --> 34:13.844
When you wake, ring for Drake

34:14.011 --> 34:17.056
Drake will bring your tray

34:17.223 --> 34:24.105
When you're through
Mrs. Pugh comes to take it away

34:27.190 --> 34:31.571
- Annie!
- Come on, Annie! Come on!

34:33.114 --> 34:36.409
No need to pick up any toys

34:36.576 --> 34:39.286
That's okay, I haven't got any anyway.

34:39.454 --> 34:45.208
No finger will you lift, my dear

34:45.376 --> 34:48.420
We have but one request

34:48.588 --> 34:51.507
Please put us to the test

34:51.674 --> 34:58.055
I know I'm gonna like it here

35:09.192 --> 35:15.156
Used to room in a tomb
Where I'd sit and freeze

35:15.323 --> 35:18.326
Get me now, holy cow

35:18.493 --> 35:22.705
Could someone pinch me, please?

35:23.456 --> 35:26.000
Hold still. Hold still!

35:26.167 --> 35:28.169
You mutt!

36:07.083 --> 36:08.334
Hi, Annie!

36:08.543 --> 36:10.878
Got something for you.

36:20.680 --> 36:22.557
Here you are, Annie.

36:26.811 --> 36:29.605
We've never had a little girl

36:29.772 --> 36:32.900
We've never had a little girl
We've never had a little girl

36:33.067 --> 36:35.903
I'm very, very, very glad to volunteer

36:36.070 --> 36:39.240
I'm glad she's glad to volunteer

36:39.407 --> 36:42.159
We hope you understand

36:42.326 --> 36:45.329
Your wish is our command

36:45.496 --> 36:51.043
- I know I'm gonna like it here
- We know you're gonna like it here

36:59.051 --> 37:01.971
It's Mr. Warbucks. Don't worry now.

37:09.270 --> 37:11.731
- Welcome home, sir.
- Did the painting arrive?

37:11.939 --> 37:14.567
They're just uncrating it, sir.

37:26.120 --> 37:28.789
I don't like it. Send it back.
Any messages?

37:29.040 --> 37:32.835
President Roosevelt called three
times. He said it was urgent.

37:33.044 --> 37:35.504
Everything's urgent to a Democrat.
What else?

37:35.713 --> 37:39.592
Mr. Rockefeller, Mr. Vanderbilt,
Mr. DuPont, Mr. Carnegie.

37:39.842 --> 37:43.971
Wait! There's something interesting
in that woman's smile.

37:44.180 --> 37:48.142
I might learn to like her.
Hang her in my bathroom.

37:48.392 --> 37:52.188
No time for dinner tonight. Send out
for an American cheese sandwich.

37:52.396 --> 37:54.565
Come, let's get started.

37:58.027 --> 37:59.987
What the devil's going on here?

38:00.237 --> 38:04.116
This is the press representative.
Your image.

38:05.618 --> 38:07.244
Oh, yes.

38:08.746 --> 38:12.875
Pick him up, Punjab.
Get him another camera.

38:23.386 --> 38:26.847
Why do I smell wet dog'?

38:29.976 --> 38:32.478
Because we gave Sandy a bath.

38:32.728 --> 38:34.146
What's this?

38:34.355 --> 38:37.733
This is Annie, the orphan
who will be staying with us.

38:37.984 --> 38:39.485
What are you talking about?

38:40.695 --> 38:44.365
They wanted to take photos of you
sharing your home with an orphan.

38:44.532 --> 38:45.700
Only for a week.

38:45.950 --> 38:49.328
This doesn't look like a boy!
Orphans are boys.

38:49.578 --> 38:52.957
You didn't say a boy. You
just said an orphan, so I got a girl.

38:53.165 --> 38:54.417
I want a boy!

38:56.168 --> 38:59.005
I've got an interesting
smile too, sir.

38:59.255 --> 39:04.385
Couldn't you learn to like me, sir?
Hang me in the bathroom?

39:04.802 --> 39:08.681
- Take them back now.
- Sir, she just got here.

39:08.931 --> 39:11.892
That's okay, Miss Farrell.
We'll be okay.

39:12.393 --> 39:17.189
It was nice meeting you anyhow.
I sure do like your place.

39:17.440 --> 39:21.527
- Thank you, Annette.
- Annie. I've had a swell time.

39:21.777 --> 39:25.448
The Asp drove us here in
a car the size of a train.

39:25.698 --> 39:27.825
And Punjab put a spell on Sandy.

39:28.409 --> 39:31.620
We made Drake sneeze.
And I played your pipe organ.

39:31.829 --> 39:34.832
Sandy got a bubble bath.

39:35.082 --> 39:38.085
I've had enough fun
to last me for years.

39:38.335 --> 39:41.630
It's a really swell idea
to have an orphan for a week.

39:42.339 --> 39:44.383
A really terrific idea.

39:44.550 --> 39:48.054
Even if it is only for your image,
even if I'm not the orphan...

39:48.220 --> 39:51.932
-...I'm glad you're doing it.
- I'm glad you approve.

39:52.141 --> 39:53.809
Let's get to work!

39:54.060 --> 39:57.188
Are you sure you need a boy?
Couldn't she stay?

39:57.438 --> 40:00.608
Whatever, but just for the week.

40:04.612 --> 40:06.781
- You know what?
- What?

40:07.031 --> 40:10.284
- I love you.
- I know.

40:10.534 --> 40:14.955
- Kiss me as only you can.
- You devil.

40:20.544 --> 40:22.588
Get away!

40:33.182 --> 40:38.187
Little girls, little girls
Everywhere I turn

40:38.354 --> 40:41.148
I can see them

40:42.608 --> 40:44.819
Little girls, little girls

40:44.985 --> 40:50.241
Night and day
I eat, sleep and breathe them

40:50.407 --> 40:53.828
I'm an ordinary woman

40:53.994 --> 40:56.789
With feelings

40:56.956 --> 41:01.043
I'd like a man to nibble on my ear

41:01.210 --> 41:06.215
But I'll admit, no man has bit

41:06.382 --> 41:11.178
So how come
I'm the mother of the year?

41:11.345 --> 41:14.640
How I hate little shoes, little socks

41:14.807 --> 41:19.520
And each little bloomer

41:20.771 --> 41:23.023
I'd have cracked years ago

41:23.190 --> 41:29.446
If it weren't for my sense of humor

41:30.322 --> 41:34.785
Some women are dripping
With diamonds

41:34.952 --> 41:39.748
Some women are dripping with pearls

41:39.915 --> 41:45.421
Lucky me, lucky me
Look at what I'm dripping with

41:45.588 --> 41:48.591
Little girls

42:10.905 --> 42:16.702
Little cheeks, little teeth
Everything around me is

42:16.869 --> 42:18.871
Little

42:20.206 --> 42:22.416
<i>If I wring little necks</i>

42:22.583 --> 42:29.465
Surely I would get an acquittal

42:29.632 --> 42:34.303
Someday I'll step on their freckles

42:34.470 --> 42:39.183
Some night I'll straighten their curls

42:39.350 --> 42:41.685
Send a flood, send the flu

42:41.852 --> 42:46.815
Anything that you can do
To little, little, little

42:48.651 --> 42:51.737
Little, little, little

42:53.822 --> 42:58.410
Little girls

43:05.501 --> 43:10.214
Someday I'll /and in the nuthouse

43:10.381 --> 43:14.510
With all the nuts and the squirrels

43:14.677 --> 43:20.099
There I'll stay, tucked away
Till the prohibition of

43:20.266 --> 43:24.687
Little

43:24.853 --> 43:28.774
Girls

43:39.952 --> 43:42.579
- Rooster!
- Sis.

43:43.831 --> 43:46.292
You're supposed to be in jail.

43:46.500 --> 43:49.128
- They let me out early.
- For good behavior.

43:49.336 --> 43:53.716
I want you to meet a friend of mine.
Lily St. Regis.

43:53.966 --> 43:57.928
- Named from the hotel.
- Room service.

43:58.178 --> 44:03.142
This afternoon, I put 10 on the nose
of a beautiful horse at 8-1.

44:03.392 --> 44:06.478
Sure enough, the scum-bum
took off and whipped the pack.

44:06.645 --> 44:07.855
No kidding?

44:08.105 --> 44:13.485
The thing is, I got delayed
and I didn't have time to cash in.

44:13.652 --> 44:18.907
Eighty bucks, sis, first thing
in the morning, guaranteed.

44:19.158 --> 44:23.329
All I need is 5 to tide me over.

44:23.954 --> 44:26.790
Not even a nickel for the subway.

44:26.999 --> 44:29.501
Come on, sis.

44:31.628 --> 44:36.759
I bet Miss Sticky-Fingers here
can loan you a lousy 5 bucks.

44:37.259 --> 44:39.303
I beg your pardon, I'm sure.

44:39.553 --> 44:43.932
But I don't stoop to what you're
incinerating.

44:44.767 --> 44:47.227
Give me back my goods, toots.

45:04.745 --> 45:06.455
Okay, Rooster.

45:06.663 --> 45:11.210
If I loan you 5 bucks, will you
take this dumb hotel out of here?

45:11.418 --> 45:13.462
I'm sorry, sis. Lily.

45:14.421 --> 45:17.299
Not even a nickel for the subway.

45:17.758 --> 45:20.177
You and her have the same mother?

45:38.821 --> 45:40.864
Rooster!

45:50.916 --> 45:55.254
Betcha he reads
Betcha she sews

45:55.421 --> 45:59.299
Maybe she's made me
A closet of clothes

45:59.466 --> 46:04.054
Maybe they're strict
As straight as a line

46:04.221 --> 46:10.102
Don't really care
As long as they're mine

46:11.520 --> 46:16.483
So maybe now this prayer's

46:16.650 --> 46:21.447
The last one of its kind

46:21.613 --> 46:26.910
Won't you please come get your baby?

46:27.077 --> 46:31.248
Maybe

46:42.718 --> 46:45.762
This room's bigger than Grant's tomb.

46:47.097 --> 46:48.682
Me too.

46:50.601 --> 46:53.061
Come on, Sandy. Come on!

46:57.357 --> 46:58.525
In conclusion...

46:58.734 --> 47:03.697
...because your country has raised its
voice loud and clear for democracy...

47:03.947 --> 47:07.034
...I will extend to you a credit line...

47:07.242 --> 47:09.828
...for 35 of my new fighter-bombers.

47:10.329 --> 47:15.000
That will come with a year's supply
of spare parts and ammunition--

47:15.250 --> 47:16.460
What's this?

47:16.668 --> 47:20.547
Sandy's not used to sleeping
by himself. He gets lonesome.

47:22.341 --> 47:23.425
Where were we?

47:24.426 --> 47:27.012
-"Ammunition," sir.
- Are you getting a lot done?

47:27.221 --> 47:30.641
I'd get a lot more done
if certain people...

47:31.808 --> 47:35.979
If Franklin Delano Roosevelt
would leave me alone.

47:36.230 --> 47:37.856
Six calls since I got home.

47:38.065 --> 47:41.652
- What's he want?
- My support for the New Deal.

47:41.902 --> 47:44.696
He is our president, sir.

47:45.113 --> 47:46.615
Punjab!

47:47.074 --> 47:51.578
Remove this animal and its young
mistress along with it.

47:52.120 --> 47:57.125
Dear Richie, this letter will serve
as confirmation of correspondence...

47:57.334 --> 48:02.172
...concerning the details
of your extended deferment.

48:03.799 --> 48:05.300
--On or before September 1.

48:05.551 --> 48:10.597
If you cannot meet that deadline,
you will be charged interest.

48:10.847 --> 48:13.976
Six percent. Cordially, et cetera.

48:16.979 --> 48:22.109
P.S. One of my companies
is developing bomb-proof glass.

48:22.484 --> 48:28.365
This may be of interest to you
if the global situation deteriorates.

48:31.660 --> 48:34.955
- What was that?
- Well done, Sandy.

48:35.163 --> 48:38.375
- Was that man trying to kill you?
- That will be all.

48:38.625 --> 48:40.836
Yes, sir. Come along, dear.

48:42.004 --> 48:44.798
- Who'd want to kill Mr. Warbucks?
- The Bolsheviks.

48:45.048 --> 48:47.509
He's proof that
the American system works...

48:47.718 --> 48:50.178
...and Bolsheviks don't
want anyone to know.

48:50.679 --> 48:53.849
The Bolsheviks? Leaping lizards!

49:04.526 --> 49:07.821
Get your dog out of my pool!

49:07.988 --> 49:11.450
He thought you were drowning.
He was trying to save your life.

49:11.617 --> 49:16.038
- Go on, you mutt. Get out of here.
- Come on.

49:26.715 --> 49:28.508
Like my suit?

49:28.842 --> 49:30.260
What? Oh, yes.

49:30.469 --> 49:32.095
Miss Farrell picked it out.

49:32.304 --> 49:37.017
- Never thought I'd get used to a girl.
- Girls are easier to get used to.

49:37.267 --> 49:41.396
Like Miss Farrell,
she does all the work around here.

49:41.647 --> 49:45.025
- You don't know her first name.
- I do. It's Grace.

49:45.233 --> 49:48.987
She thinks you're the greatest thing
since sliced bread.

49:49.196 --> 49:50.238
I beg your pardon.

49:50.447 --> 49:54.826
I know it's none of my business,
but you never notice anything.

49:58.789 --> 50:00.874
Sliced bread.

50:01.583 --> 50:06.713
Wilhelm, please offer your son my
congratulations on his engagement.

50:07.172 --> 50:11.134
Hold on. Buy copper.

50:11.385 --> 50:16.515
Tell the crown prince
that my yacht in Monte Carlo...

50:16.765 --> 50:21.728
...is entirely at his disposal.

50:21.937 --> 50:25.482
Hold on. More copper.

50:25.691 --> 50:29.486
- Don't encourage her, Punjab.
- Maybe I should take her out.

50:29.736 --> 50:34.950
- Where do you want to go?
- To meet President Roosevelt.

50:36.910 --> 50:42.040
- How about a movie?
- Pepper went to a movie once.

50:42.332 --> 50:46.503
She said it was swell,
and Miss Hannigan goes all the time.

50:46.753 --> 50:50.924
- Take her to the Radio City Music Hall.
- Aren't you going to take me?

50:51.174 --> 50:55.011
Me? Annie, you may think
that Miss Farrell does all the work...

50:55.262 --> 50:59.057
...but I'm a very busy man.

50:59.307 --> 51:02.185
I know. Didn't mean
to get in the way, Mr. Warbucks.

51:02.394 --> 51:06.356
Nobody has to take me.
I'll go practice my backhand.

51:10.902 --> 51:15.949
Pepper lies a lot. She probably
hasn't been to a movie either.

51:16.616 --> 51:20.746
Actually, I think it's better when
you don't know what you're missing.

51:23.707 --> 51:29.629
Punjab, buy out the 8:00 show.
Let's all go to the movies.

51:34.176 --> 51:39.765
- You should leave your hair down.
- No, I couldn't.

51:39.931 --> 51:42.601
Miss Hannigan says
a man don't look at your brains.

51:42.768 --> 51:44.644
Oh, really? My goodness.

51:44.811 --> 51:47.689
Come on, let's go to the movies.

51:47.939 --> 51:50.400
Let's go see the stars.

51:51.234 --> 51:53.445
Cowboy heroes

51:53.612 --> 51:55.405
Cops and robbers

51:55.572 --> 51:57.491
Glamour and strife

51:57.657 --> 52:00.118
Bigger than life

52:03.914 --> 52:08.043
Sitting in the darkness

52:08.210 --> 52:12.380
What a world to see

52:12.547 --> 52:16.551
Let's go to the movies, Annie

52:16.718 --> 52:21.598
Wait and see

52:23.058 --> 52:24.893
Bette Davis is probably lying

52:25.060 --> 52:27.145
And Greta Garbo is probably crying

52:27.312 --> 52:31.733
While Robert Taylor
Is locked in her dying embrace

52:31.900 --> 52:36.071
Chico and Groucho and Chaplin
And Lloyd are all super

52:36.238 --> 52:37.906
Sweet Mickey Mouse
Shirley Temple

52:38.073 --> 52:39.574
And dear Jackie Cooper

52:39.741 --> 52:43.328
Let's go to the movies

52:43.495 --> 52:47.916
Let's go see the stars

52:52.087 --> 52:54.297
Fred and Ginger

52:54.464 --> 52:56.842
Spinning madly

53:13.567 --> 53:18.488
Anything you can imagine

53:20.407 --> 53:22.576
Songs and romance

53:22.742 --> 53:25.161
Life is a dance

53:27.664 --> 53:32.002
Sitting in the darkness

53:32.168 --> 53:36.590
Popcorn on your knee

53:36.756 --> 53:40.886
Give the maid the night off

53:42.178 --> 53:45.223
Turn the kitchen light off.

53:45.640 --> 53:50.186
Let's go to the movies, Annie

53:50.353 --> 53:55.025
You and me

54:22.886 --> 54:26.348
Welcome to the movies

54:26.514 --> 54:30.143
Welcome to the stars

54:30.310 --> 54:33.855
Welcome to this
Grand illusion

54:34.022 --> 54:35.732
All of it's yours

54:35.899 --> 54:37.901
Right through these doors

54:39.778 --> 54:43.281
Every plot's a dilly

54:43.448 --> 54:46.785
This we guarantee

54:47.160 --> 54:50.789
Welcome to the movies

54:51.122 --> 54:54.084
Wait and see

55:12.352 --> 55:14.688
Let's go to the movies

55:16.564 --> 55:20.735
Let's go see the stars

55:20.902 --> 55:23.321
Headlines holler

55:23.488 --> 55:25.156
Big depression

55:25.323 --> 55:27.367
What do we care?

55:27.534 --> 55:29.911
Movies are there

55:30.286 --> 55:34.457
Only happy endings
Boy get's girl

55:34.624 --> 55:38.545
That's our recipe

55:38.712 --> 55:41.965
Welcome to our lovely

55:42.132 --> 55:45.844
M-O- V-I-E

56:18.585 --> 56:21.796
We love to go to RKO

56:21.963 --> 56:25.258
Columbia, Universal

56:25.425 --> 56:28.678
Jack Warner and Sam Goldwyn and

56:28.845 --> 56:32.432
MGM and Zanuck
Here's to

56:32.599 --> 56:35.018
Dreams of glory

56:35.185 --> 56:37.562
Cast of thousands

