01:22:20.645 --> 01:22:24.482
You're never fully dressed
Without a smile

01:22:33.783 --> 01:22:36.202
You're never fully dressed
Without a smile

01:22:36.369 --> 01:22:39.205
Who cares what they're wearing

01:22:39.372 --> 01:22:42.542
On Main Street or Savile Row

01:22:42.709 --> 01:22:46.212
It's what you wear from ear to ear

01:22:46.379 --> 01:22:50.091
And not from head to toe

01:22:50.592 --> 01:22:55.221
That matters

01:22:56.931 --> 01:23:00.685
So, senator
So, janitor

01:23:00.852 --> 01:23:03.480
So long for a while

01:23:03.647 --> 01:23:06.733
Remember you're never fully dressed

01:23:06.900 --> 01:23:10.320
Though you may wear the best

01:23:10.487 --> 01:23:13.365
You're never fully dressed

01:23:13.531 --> 01:23:16.701
Without a smile

01:23:16.868 --> 01:23:23.083
You're never fully dressed
You're never fully dressed

01:23:23.249 --> 01:23:24.501
Without a--

01:23:25.418 --> 01:23:28.880
Do I hear happiness in here?

01:23:42.811 --> 01:23:44.521
They never miss.

01:23:47.357 --> 01:23:49.693
Everybody's
going to get their chance.

01:23:54.155 --> 01:23:56.783
Annie, it's your mother.

01:24:01.413 --> 01:24:04.749
We've got to get her out of here.
We can't expose her to this.

01:24:04.916 --> 01:24:06.751
Get the autocopter ready.

01:24:28.690 --> 01:24:33.069
Guess what. Mr. Warbucks is going
to take you to see the president.

01:24:33.903 --> 01:24:36.197
Oh, boy!

01:24:58.470 --> 01:25:02.140
Marvelous!
Aren't Republicans ostentatious?

01:25:02.390 --> 01:25:07.061
Franklin, behave.
It's astonishing he's here at all.

01:25:11.107 --> 01:25:16.237
- What do you call this, Oliver?
- An autocopter.

01:25:16.571 --> 01:25:21.701
You don't need an airport.
They say it can land on a dime.

01:25:21.951 --> 01:25:26.748
- Whatever that may be.
- You being here means a great deal.

01:25:26.915 --> 01:25:33.338
It means nothing. It means only
that Annie wanted to meet you.

01:25:35.632 --> 01:25:40.762
- Nice to meet you, Mr. President.
- It's my pleasure, Annie.

01:25:41.137 --> 01:25:44.808
Thank you for bringing the old goat.
Make a New Dealer of him yet.

01:25:45.058 --> 01:25:48.269
- Inconceivable.
- Don't mind him, Oliver.

01:25:48.520 --> 01:25:50.104
Come along, Annie.

01:25:50.313 --> 01:25:55.443
My Uncle Theodore used to teach
his children to walk on stilts.

01:25:55.819 --> 01:25:59.656
I can't teach you that, I can teach you
to roll in a chair with wheels.

01:25:59.823 --> 01:26:01.491
My own private roller coaster.

01:26:02.325 --> 01:26:06.746
The New Deal is badly planned,
badly organized and administered.

01:26:06.996 --> 01:26:09.874
You don't think your
programs through.

01:26:10.124 --> 01:26:13.044
Think what you're going to do
to the economy!

01:26:13.253 --> 01:26:17.131
- People don't eat in the long run.
- People can't feed their children.

01:26:17.340 --> 01:26:19.551
The lucky ones are left in orphanages.

01:26:19.801 --> 01:26:22.178
The older ones steal, starve.

01:26:22.387 --> 01:26:25.056
This business
of this country is business--

01:26:25.306 --> 01:26:29.602
Take them off the dole and put
them to work. That's what I'll do.

01:26:29.811 --> 01:26:35.733
In the National Parks, clearing trails,
fighting fires, planting trees.

01:26:35.900 --> 01:26:38.862
- Hold it.
- I want to feed them and house them...

01:26:39.028 --> 01:26:40.071
...and pay them.

01:26:40.280 --> 01:26:42.365
Enough to send home
to their parents...

01:26:42.532 --> 01:26:46.619
...so they can hold their heads up
and be proud to be Americans.

01:26:46.786 --> 01:26:50.039
- That's a swell idea.
- It isn't a swell idea, Annie...

01:26:50.206 --> 01:26:52.000
...it's mistaken foolishness.

01:26:52.166 --> 01:26:54.377
Big-hearted and empty-headed.

01:26:54.586 --> 01:26:58.464
Which parks? Which children?
What will it cost?

01:26:58.715 --> 01:27:01.467
Who's going to organize it?
Who's going to run it?

01:27:02.677 --> 01:27:06.389
- I was hoping you would.
- Me?

01:27:06.598 --> 01:27:10.435
- And Annie.
- Leaping lizards!

01:27:10.935 --> 01:27:13.897
- Out of the question.
- How can I help?

01:27:14.147 --> 01:27:15.523
Wait a minute!

01:27:15.732 --> 01:27:18.693
- You can help recruit young people.
- Hold everything!

01:27:18.943 --> 01:27:23.156
They think their government
doesn't care whether they live or die.

01:27:23.406 --> 01:27:26.492
With your help,
we could convince them otherwise-

01:27:26.743 --> 01:27:28.286
I want to say something.

01:27:28.536 --> 01:27:33.082
There's a song I used to sing
in the orphanage when I was sad.

01:27:33.333 --> 01:27:36.878
- It always cheered me up.
- Eleanor!

01:27:37.670 --> 01:27:41.925
Just thinking about tomorrow

01:27:42.091 --> 01:27:47.138
Clears away the cobwebs
And the sorrow

01:27:47.305 --> 01:27:49.807
Till there's none

01:27:49.974 --> 01:27:52.310
When I'm stuck with a day

01:27:52.477 --> 01:27:56.189
That's gray and lonely

01:27:56.356 --> 01:27:58.650
I just stick out my chin

01:27:58.816 --> 01:28:03.821
And grin and say

01:28:06.449 --> 01:28:09.702
<i>The sun 'll come out tomorrow</i>

01:28:09.869 --> 01:28:14.540
<i>So you gotta hang on till tomorrow</i>

01:28:14.707 --> 01:28:18.044
Come what may

01:28:18.211 --> 01:28:21.047
Tomorrow, tomorrow

01:28:21.214 --> 01:28:24.175
I love ya, tomorrow

01:28:24.342 --> 01:28:29.305
You're only a day away

01:28:32.183 --> 01:28:34.936
Oh, Franklin.

01:28:36.980 --> 01:28:40.400
You'll help us too, won't you, Oliver?

01:28:40.817 --> 01:28:43.236
Think of the children.
Think of Annie.

01:28:45.029 --> 01:28:47.949
<i>The sun 'll come out tomorrow</i>

01:28:48.116 --> 01:28:52.328
Sing, Oliver, that's an order
from your commander in chief.

01:28:52.996 --> 01:28:55.289
There 'll be sun

01:28:55.456 --> 01:28:56.666
- Eleanor?
- I can't sing.

01:28:56.874 --> 01:28:58.251
Sing.

01:28:59.585 --> 01:29:03.840
Clears away the cobwebs
And the sorrow

01:29:04.007 --> 01:29:05.049
Till there's none

01:29:05.216 --> 01:29:06.551
Solo for the president.

01:29:06.718 --> 01:29:08.720
When I'm stuck with a day

01:29:08.886 --> 01:29:11.180
That's gray and lonely

01:29:11.764 --> 01:29:13.975
I just stick out my chin

01:29:14.142 --> 01:29:17.020
And grin and say

01:29:17.186 --> 01:29:20.523
Everybody! Republicans too, Oliver.
Sing!

01:29:20.898 --> 01:29:24.068
<i>The sun 'll come out tomorrow</i>

01:29:24.235 --> 01:29:28.322
So you've got to hang on till tomorrow

01:29:28.489 --> 01:29:30.408
Come what may

01:29:30.575 --> 01:29:31.617
Harmony!

01:29:31.784 --> 01:29:34.120
Tomorrow, tomorrow

01:29:34.287 --> 01:29:36.831
I love ya, tomorrow

01:29:36.998 --> 01:29:41.252
You're only a day away

01:29:41.419 --> 01:29:44.964
Tomorrow, tomorrow

01:29:45.131 --> 01:29:47.800
I love ya, tomorrow

01:29:47.967 --> 01:29:52.096
You're only a day

01:29:52.263 --> 01:29:59.062
A Way

01:30:03.274 --> 01:30:08.404
All right, everybody, step up.
I've got fresh fish here.

01:30:21.042 --> 01:30:25.505
- Do you run this establishment?
- Unfortunately.

01:30:25.713 --> 01:30:30.218
Ten years ago, we left our
little baby girl on the front steps.

01:30:30.468 --> 01:30:36.140
There was a job managing a hotel,
but only if we had no children.

01:30:36.349 --> 01:30:41.229
- Wrap it up.
- We never meant to leave Annie.

01:30:42.939 --> 01:30:46.776
Now we have a hardware store in
New Jersey. We can take care of her.

01:30:47.026 --> 01:30:48.528
We've always loved her.

01:30:49.862 --> 01:30:54.826
- You're Annie's parents?
- We live over the store.

01:30:55.618 --> 01:30:58.496
- There's a yard out back.
- With chickens.

01:30:58.746 --> 01:31:00.748
And a rooster.

01:31:05.503 --> 01:31:07.004
Rooster?

01:31:10.716 --> 01:31:15.346
My God! I never would
have recognized you.

01:31:19.934 --> 01:31:23.688
If we can fool you,
we can fool "Big Bucks."

01:31:23.980 --> 01:31:27.859
- Fifty thousand smackers.
- You'll be the death of me.

01:31:28.067 --> 01:31:32.697
Sis, this is going to be
the best bunco job ever.

01:31:32.947 --> 01:31:38.077
- We need details.
- About Annie. Specifics.

01:31:38.703 --> 01:31:43.416
- What's in it for me'?
- A three-way split of the $50,000.

01:31:43.666 --> 01:31:46.210
- I want half.
- All right, half!

01:31:46.377 --> 01:31:48.713
- Rooster!
- All right!

01:31:48.880 --> 01:31:53.718
Twenty-five grand for me and Lil,
25 grand for you.

01:31:56.512 --> 01:31:59.765
Why don't we wait
and see what she's got.

01:32:00.433 --> 01:32:03.936
See if it's worth 25 grand.

01:32:04.187 --> 01:32:07.398
You want details? I've got details.

01:32:07.565 --> 01:32:10.193
I've got specifics on every kid
in this dump.

01:32:10.359 --> 01:32:13.196
It's just finding the right box.

01:32:15.448 --> 01:32:19.577
Annie wears a locket around her neck.

01:32:20.453 --> 01:32:22.496
It's a broken locket.

01:32:22.705 --> 01:32:27.710
She says her parents saved the other
half to come and claim her with.

01:32:28.169 --> 01:32:33.007
Years ago,
her parents were killed in a fire.

01:32:33.633 --> 01:32:35.718
The cops brought me all their junk.

01:32:35.927 --> 01:32:38.137
Well, my darling baby brother...

01:32:38.304 --> 01:32:42.975
...if Annie's parents can claim her
with that locket, so can we.

01:32:43.768 --> 01:32:48.189
- Fifty thousand smackers.
- The kid we'll drop in the river.

01:32:48.439 --> 01:32:52.026
They're going to do
something bad to Annie!

01:32:52.235 --> 01:32:55.238
- Have you cleaned the can?
- Listen to me. I mean it.

01:32:55.446 --> 01:32:56.822
Clean the can!

01:32:57.031 --> 01:33:01.535
- Duffy, Tessie, somebody!
- Do you want a knuckle sandwich?

01:33:01.786 --> 01:33:04.205
- We've got to warn Annie!
- Scrub!

01:33:04.830 --> 01:33:07.875
It's in a sealed envelope.

01:33:08.042 --> 01:33:11.587
It ain't fair how we scrounge
For three or four bucks

01:33:11.754 --> 01:33:13.089
While she gets Warbucks

01:33:13.256 --> 01:33:15.508
The little brat. Look in those!

01:33:15.675 --> 01:33:18.636
It ain't fair
This here life is driving me nuts

01:33:18.803 --> 01:33:20.054
Make yourself useful!

01:33:20.221 --> 01:33:22.139
When we get peanuts

01:33:22.974 --> 01:33:24.392
She's living fat

01:33:24.809 --> 01:33:26.644
Maybe she holds the key

01:33:26.811 --> 01:33:29.438
- That little lady
- To getting more bucks

01:33:29.605 --> 01:33:32.483
- Right, instead of less.
- It'll have her name on it.

01:33:32.650 --> 01:33:37.655
Maybe we fix it again
With something shady

01:33:37.822 --> 01:33:40.866
Where does that put us?

01:33:44.578 --> 01:33:46.497
Give you one guess

01:33:50.835 --> 01:33:51.961
Open it.

01:33:55.298 --> 01:33:57.550
Hurry.

01:34:00.094 --> 01:34:02.138
Easy Street

01:34:04.515 --> 01:34:07.935
Easy Street

01:34:08.227 --> 01:34:14.817
- Annie is the key
- Yes, sirree

01:34:16.986 --> 01:34:20.239
<i>- Easy Street
- We'll live the plush life</i>

01:34:20.406 --> 01:34:23.784
- Easy Street
- The lazy, lush life

01:34:23.951 --> 01:34:27.330
Better get there

01:34:29.874 --> 01:34:31.917
The gravy's flowing there

01:34:33.836 --> 01:34:35.963
We'll soon be going there

01:34:36.130 --> 01:34:40.259
Where you sleep till noon

01:34:40.426 --> 01:34:42.303
Yeah, yeah, yeah

01:34:44.513 --> 01:34:48.517
- Move them feet
- Move them ever-loving feet

01:34:48.684 --> 01:34:52.063
- To Easy Street
- Where living's sweet

01:34:52.229 --> 01:34:56.067
That's where we're gonna be

01:34:57.610 --> 01:35:00.571
Easy Street

01:35:01.655 --> 01:35:04.408
Easy Street

01:36:15.646 --> 01:36:20.192
Move them feet to Easy Street

01:36:21.235 --> 01:36:31.829
That's where we're gonna

01:36:44.800 --> 01:36:46.469
Hit it, sis.

01:36:56.395 --> 01:37:01.442
That's where we're gonna

01:37:01.609 --> 01:37:03.819
Stay

01:37:08.699 --> 01:37:13.204
Easy Street

01:37:22.963 --> 01:37:25.341
Now do the other one.

01:37:34.600 --> 01:37:38.479
Duffy, Tessie, somebody! They're
going to do something to Annie!

01:37:38.687 --> 01:37:40.397
- Who is?
- They are!

01:37:40.648 --> 01:37:42.441
- Who's they?
- Miss Hannigan.

01:37:42.691 --> 01:37:44.318
Oh, my goodness!

01:37:48.822 --> 01:37:50.783
Beautiful.

01:37:57.456 --> 01:38:01.627
- Where do you think you're going?
- Run, run, go tell Annie!

01:38:02.753 --> 01:38:04.338
Stop them.

01:38:13.264 --> 01:38:14.974
Get in that closet.

01:38:16.559 --> 01:38:18.727
Stop it!

01:38:23.816 --> 01:38:27.069
Whose rotten idea was this?

01:39:02.187 --> 01:39:04.189
Are they here?

01:39:04.440 --> 01:39:08.402
A man who counts his chickens before
they hatch gets a scrambled egg.

01:39:08.569 --> 01:39:10.195
What?

01:39:14.033 --> 01:39:19.330
- Have my parents come for me?
- We haven't found them.

01:39:45.481 --> 01:39:50.611
I interviewed 865 couples.
None of them knew about the locket.

01:39:51.904 --> 01:39:55.908
I never realized how many dishonest
people there are in New York.

01:40:17.388 --> 01:40:23.060
They're dead. I guess I've known
that deep down for a long time.

01:40:23.227 --> 01:40:26.355
I'm not giving up, so don't you.

01:40:26.522 --> 01:40:31.151
I didn't want to be just another
orphan. I wanted to be special.

01:40:31.402 --> 01:40:35.948
You are special.
Never stop believing that.

01:40:36.782 --> 01:40:39.076
We're trapped.

01:40:44.289 --> 01:40:47.626
Oh, my goodness. Oh, my goodness.

01:40:48.961 --> 01:40:52.423
- We'll never get out of here.
- I've got an idea.

01:40:54.258 --> 01:40:57.845
Great idea.

01:40:58.971 --> 01:41:01.807
- It's heavy.
- Don't drop it.

01:41:05.310 --> 01:41:08.897
- All right.
- Now what do you want to do?

01:41:11.108 --> 01:41:15.028
She'll be so mad if she catches us.

01:41:15.195 --> 01:41:19.575
I'm not so sure I want to do this.
We'll be in so much trouble.

01:41:19.825 --> 01:41:23.495
- Duffy, hand me something.
- Here.

01:41:32.045 --> 01:41:35.340
- There's space up here.
- Be careful.

01:41:36.049 --> 01:41:39.762
Oh, my goodness. Oh, my goodness.

01:41:40.012 --> 01:41:42.055
Help me get UP-

01:41:51.607 --> 01:41:53.901
Give me your hand.

01:41:57.279 --> 01:42:00.824
It's a long way down.
Are you sure you want to do this?

01:42:05.162 --> 01:42:07.498
- Wish me luck.
- Good luck.

01:42:26.892 --> 01:42:32.523
We were starving. We needed the job
That's why we left our little girl.

01:42:32.689 --> 01:42:39.446
- Wrapped in a newspaper.
- On the steps of the orphanage.

01:42:47.579 --> 01:42:48.789
What's this?

01:42:49.039 --> 01:42:52.334
This is Ralph and Shirley Mudge
from Hoboken, New Jersey.

01:42:52.501 --> 01:42:53.794
Annie!

01:42:58.048 --> 01:43:03.178
Ralph, look!
She still has the locket.

01:43:17.901 --> 01:43:20.028
We finally found you.

01:43:20.279 --> 01:43:22.823
You heard about the reward
on the radio.

01:43:23.073 --> 01:43:25.534
- Reward?
- We don't have a radio.

01:43:25.784 --> 01:43:27.411
- In the paper.
- Paper?

01:43:27.661 --> 01:43:30.706
- What paper?
- How did you know Annie was here?

01:43:30.956 --> 01:43:35.669
- The lady at the orphanage told us.
- I have her birth certificate here.

01:43:37.337 --> 01:43:42.426
I've kept it close to my heart
all of these years.

01:43:46.805 --> 01:43:48.765
"Ann Marie Mudge.

01:43:49.016 --> 01:43:54.146
October 18, 1922."

01:44:00.068 --> 01:44:01.987
I'll go pack.

01:44:04.531 --> 01:44:07.618
Do you want me to help, baby?

01:44:08.952 --> 01:44:10.621
No, thanks...

01:44:11.371 --> 01:44:13.040
...Mom.

01:44:42.861 --> 01:44:44.613
Come on.

01:45:02.255 --> 01:45:04.549
A certified check!

01:45:05.592 --> 01:45:09.972
We're so glad to have found Annie.
We don't need this.

01:45:10.222 --> 01:45:16.103
- I'll take it back.
- Of course, we are poor people.

01:45:17.145 --> 01:45:19.398
It would help us a lot.

01:45:19.648 --> 01:45:24.611
We could buy her milk,
a warm blanket.

01:45:26.363 --> 01:45:31.243
Put it in your pocket, Mrs. Mudge.

01:45:36.123 --> 01:45:38.125
Come on, you guys.

01:45:40.085 --> 01:45:45.215
- Oh, my goodness!
- We're never going to make it.

01:45:45.465 --> 01:45:49.803
- We've found Fifth Avenue.
- Number one, Fifth Avenue.

01:45:50.012 --> 01:45:53.348
We've got to go to 987.

01:45:54.266 --> 01:45:58.145
- Molly, get on my back.
- Come on, you guys, help.

01:46:02.274 --> 01:46:07.112
- Will the stores take this back?
- All your new clothes?

01:46:08.030 --> 01:46:10.907
I guess so.
Don't you want to keep them?

01:46:11.158 --> 01:46:16.288
My folks are poor. All these clothes
are going to make them feel bad.

01:46:16.496 --> 01:46:22.377
- Take them to the orphanage.
- Certainly.

01:46:22.753 --> 01:46:25.464
This will look so cute on Molly.

01:46:28.008 --> 01:46:30.469
This will look good on Duffy.

01:46:44.024 --> 01:46:48.278
Betcha my life
Is gonna be swell

01:46:48.445 --> 01:46:49.905
Looking at them

01:46:50.072 --> 01:46:54.076
It's easy to tell

01:46:54.451 --> 01:46:58.371
And maybe I'll forget

01:46:58.538 --> 01:47:02.292
How nice he was to me

01:47:03.168 --> 01:47:09.549
And how I was almost his baby

01:47:32.489 --> 01:47:34.491
It'll be fine

01:47:34.658 --> 01:47:36.576
Nothing to fear

01:47:36.743 --> 01:47:40.455
She'll be as happy
As she was here

01:47:40.622 --> 01:47:44.126
Things have worked out
Much better than planned

01:47:44.292 --> 01:47:46.128
It makes you smile

01:47:46.294 --> 01:47:49.214
When fate takes a hand

01:47:51.550 --> 01:47:54.386
<i>And I know I'll forget</i>

01:47:54.553 --> 01:47:57.889
How much she meant to me

01:47:58.056 --> 01:48:04.187
And how she was almost my baby

01:48:05.230 --> 01:48:08.150
Maybe

01:48:35.760 --> 01:48:37.512
- Did you get it?
- She has it.

01:48:37.679 --> 01:48:39.347
Let me see it.

01:48:40.140 --> 01:48:45.270
- I'd better keep it.
- Over my dead body.

01:48:45.478 --> 01:48:48.398
That's the brightest thing I've
ever heard you say.

01:48:48.565 --> 01:48:50.066
Ladies! Ladies!

01:48:50.233 --> 01:48:54.112
